<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10653</anchor> <rss>erct-0025.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0025</addr>  <route>erct-0025.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Retract</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0025.agda" type="external">erct-0025.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>When <tex>s \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a section of <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>, we say that <tex>A</tex> is a <em><strong>retract</strong></em> of <tex>B</tex>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10654</anchor> <rss>erct-003L.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-003L</addr>  <route>erct-003L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Z.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Z" title="Functions and inverses">Functions and inverses</link> › basic definitions</title> <parent>erct-000Z</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10655</anchor> <rss>erct-001Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001Q</addr>  <route>erct-001Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Fiber</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001Q.agda" type="external">erct-001Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The <em><strong>fiber</strong></em> of a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> at an element <tex>b:B</tex> is the type consisting of elements <tex>a \colon  A</tex> equipped with identifications <tex>p \colon  fa=b</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10656</anchor> <rss>erct-0014.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0014</addr>  <route>erct-0014.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Homotopy</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0014.agda" type="external">erct-0014.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f , g  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> be two dependent functions. A <em><strong>homotopy</strong></em> from <tex>f</tex> to <tex>g</tex>, writing <tex>H \colon  f  \sim  g</tex> is given by a dependent function <tex>H \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } fx=gx</tex>. We shall write <tex>1_{ f } \colon  f  \sim  f</tex> for the <em><strong>identity homotopy</strong></em> on <tex>f</tex> defined by <tex>1_{ f } x: \equiv   \mathsf {refl}</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10657</anchor> <rss>erct-000Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000Y</addr>  <route>erct-000Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Section-retraction pair</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000Y.agda" type="external">erct-000Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>s  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> and <tex>r  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a pair of maps. A homotopy <tex>h  \colon  r \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibits <tex>s</tex> as a <em><strong>section</strong></em> of <tex>r</tex> and <tex>r</tex> as a <em><strong>retraction</strong></em> of <tex>s</tex>. Together, <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( s,r \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> are referred to as a <em><strong>section-retraction pair</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10658</anchor> <rss>erct-0025.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0025</addr>  <route>erct-0025.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Retract</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0025.agda" type="external">erct-0025.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>When <tex>s \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a section of <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>, we say that <tex>A</tex> is a <em><strong>retract</strong></em> of <tex>B</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10659</anchor> <rss>erct-000U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000U</addr>  <route>erct-000U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Biinverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>biinverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a pair of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> to <tex>f</tex>. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with a biinverse as a <em><strong>biinvertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10660</anchor> <rss>erct-000X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000X</addr>  <route>erct-000X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Quasi-inverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000X.agda" type="external">erct-000X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>quasi-inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a function <tex>g  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> equipped with homotopies <tex>\epsilon \colon  f  \circ  g  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and <tex>\eta \colon  g  \circ  f  \sim 1_{ A }</tex>, rendering <tex>g</tex> simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p><p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <tex>\eta</tex> and <tex>\epsilon</tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <em>unit</em> and <em>counit</em> of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10661</anchor> <rss>erct-000W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000W</addr>  <route>erct-000W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <tex>\chi   \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</tex> in <tex>f \circ  g  \circ  f  \sim  f</tex> relating the (<em>a priori</em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with an inverse as an <em><strong>invertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10662</anchor> <rss>erct-003K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-003K</addr>  <route>erct-003K.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>15</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Embedding</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003K.agda" type="external">erct-003K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called an <em><strong>embedding</strong></em> when for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> the action on identifications <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  x=y \to  fx=fy</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10663</anchor> <rss>erct-000V.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000V</addr>  <route>erct-000V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Equivalence of types</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000V.agda" type="external">erct-000V.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>equivalence</strong></em> from <tex>A</tex> to <tex>B</tex> is defined to be a function <tex>A  \to  B</tex> equipped with a  <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverse</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10664</anchor> <rss>erct-0044.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0044</addr>  <route>erct-0044.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0044.agda" type="external">erct-0044.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>, the type of <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverses</link> to <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10665</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-0044</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Without loss of generality, we may assume that <tex>f</tex> has an <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g, \epsilon , \eta , \chi \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>. By <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to argue that the type of <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">inverses</link> to <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>; the type of <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">inverses</link> to <tex>f</tex> is in fact equivalent to the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> equipped with a <link href="erct-0041.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0041" title="The coherent remainder of a section">coherent remainder</link>:</p>
 <tex display="block">    \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( \sigma : \mathsf {section} \, f \right ) \mathclose {} } }     \mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma   </tex>

 <p>By <ref addr="erct-001M" href="erct-001M.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to show that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> to <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> and that for every such <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link>, the <link href="erct-0041.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0041" title="The coherent remainder of a section">coherent remainder</link> thereof is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. The latter is <ref addr="erct-0043" href="erct-0043.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, and the former follows from <ref addr="erct-002Q" href="erct-002Q.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> by means of the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g, \eta \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10666</anchor> <rss>erct-0043.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0043</addr>  <route>erct-0043.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The <link href="erct-0041.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0041" title="The coherent remainder of a section">coherent remainder</link> of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0043.agda" type="external">erct-0043.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\sigma \equiv \mathopen {} \left ( g \colon  B \to  A, \epsilon \colon  f \circ  g = 1_{ B } \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>. Then the <link href="erct-0041.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0041" title="The coherent remainder of a section">coherent remainder</link> of <tex>\sigma</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10667</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-0043</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, we may argue that <tex>\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. We let <tex>P</tex> be the following type defined using <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">path object</link> structure of <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fibers</link> given in <ref addr="erct-001R" href="erct-001R.xml" taxon="Example"/>:</p>
 <tex display="block">    \begin {aligned}    P &amp;: \equiv      \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }      \mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} , \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {}      \cong _{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} }     \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}      \\     P &amp; \equiv      \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }      \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p : g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  = x \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p : g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  = x \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p : g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  = x \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p : g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {}  = x \right ) \mathclose {} } }      \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \mathsf {act}_{ f } p \cdot   \mathsf {refl}     \end {aligned}  </tex>

 <p>It is not difficult to show using <ref addr="erct-0042" href="erct-0042.xml" taxon="Definition"/> that <tex>\mathsf {coherentRemainder}_{ f } \sigma</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>P</tex>; we will not need the further fact that it is <em>equivalent</em> to <tex>P</tex>.</p>

 <p>Therefore, it remains to show that <tex>P</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. Without loss of generality, we may assume that we have some <tex>h: P</tex>. By <ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>, we may fix <tex>x:A</tex> and prove that <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} , \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} \cong _{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} } \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. Of course, this is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the identification type <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( g \mathopen {} \left ( f x \right ) \mathclose {} , \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} =_{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} } \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> and so by <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> it is enough to prove that the latter is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>. In fact, we will deduce this via <ref addr="erct-002T" href="erct-002T.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> by observing that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> at <tex>fx</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>: using our assumption <tex>h:P</tex> and the distributivity of products over sums, we may construct a retraction of <tex>f</tex> exhibiting <tex>f</tex> as <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and thus by <ref addr="erct-002N" href="erct-002N.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10668</anchor> <rss>erct-003S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003S</addr>  <route>erct-003S.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of an <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> type is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10669</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-003S</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>; the base cases for <tex>n=-2</tex> and <tex>n=-1</tex> are given by <ref addr="erct-002V" href="erct-002V.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> and <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> respectively. In the inductive step, we assume that <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> exhibits <tex>B</tex> as a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and that for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=_Ay</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> to show that for all <tex>u,v:B</tex> the identification type <tex>u=_Bv</tex> is likewise <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link>. The result follows from our assumption and the fact that <tex>u=_Bv</tex> is (by <ref addr="erct-003U" href="erct-003U.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>) a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>su=_Asv</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10670</anchor> <rss>erct-003Z.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003Z</addr>  <route>erct-003Z.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Dependent product of <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be an arbitrary type and let <tex>B \colon  A \to \mathsf {Type}</tex> be a family of <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types. Then the dependent product <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10671</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-003Z</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>, with the base cases following from <ref addr="erct-001A" href="erct-001A.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> respectively. In the inductive step, we need to show that for all <tex>f,g \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> the identification type <tex>f=g</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> assuming the same for the identification types of each <tex>Bx</tex>. By <ref addr="erct-0015" href="erct-0015.xml" taxon="Axiom"/>, <tex>f=g</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } fx=gx</tex> and the latter is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> by our inductive hypothesis. Therefore, the result follows from <ref addr="erct-003S" href="erct-003S.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10672</anchor> <rss>erct-003W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003W</addr>  <route>erct-003W.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Dependent sum of <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003W.agda" type="external">erct-003W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>A</tex> be <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> and let <tex>B \colon  A \to \mathsf {Type}</tex> be a family of <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link> types. Then the dependent sum <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10673</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-003W</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By induction on <tex>n</tex>, with the base cases following from <ref addr="erct-003V" href="erct-003V.xml" taxon="Corollary"/> and <ref addr="erct-001M" href="erct-001M.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>. In the inductive step, we need to show that for all <tex>u,v \colon \mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> the identification type <tex>u=v</tex> is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> assuming the same of all the identification types of <tex>A</tex> and <tex>Bx</tex> for <tex>x:A</tex>. By <ref addr="erct-0035" href="erct-0035.xml" taxon="Definition"/>, <tex>u=v</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p:u.1=v.1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p:u.1=v.1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p:u.1=v.1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( p:u.1=v.1 \right ) \mathclose {} } }  p_*u.2=v.2</tex> and the latter is <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n+1</tex>-truncated</span></link> by our inductive hypothesis; thus the result follows from <ref addr="erct-003S" href="erct-003S.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10674</anchor> <rss>erct-003U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-003U</addr>  <route>erct-003U.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>17</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Lifting <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link> to identifications</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003U.agda" type="external">erct-003U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>s \colon  A \to  B</tex> exhibit <tex>A</tex> as a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>B</tex>; then <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ s } \colon  x = y \to  sx=sy</tex> exhibits <tex>x=y</tex> as a retract of <tex>sx=sy</tex> for each <tex>x,y:A</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10675</anchor> <rss>erct-002Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Q</addr>  <route>erct-002Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">Sections</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> are unique</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Q.agda" type="external">erct-002Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of some <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10676</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002Q</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for dependent function spaces</link>, we can see that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex>, using the <link href="erct-0023.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0023" title="Path object structure on sections">univalence principle for sections</link>.</p>

 <p>To show that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex> already, we know that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002N" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">therefore</link> that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>. By <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to show that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, which follows via <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-002O" href="erct-002O.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10677</anchor> <rss>erct-002R.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002R</addr>  <route>erct-002R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">Retractions</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> are unique</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002R.agda" type="external">erct-002R.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of some <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10678</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002R</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Analogous to the <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002Q" title="Sections of sections are unique">corresponding result for sections of sections</link>, using the fact that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> can be seen to be a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>- \circ  f</tex> at <tex>1_{ A }</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10679</anchor> <rss>erct-0026.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-0026</addr>  <route>erct-0026.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">Propositions</link> are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0026.agda" type="external">erct-0026.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10680</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-0026</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>This can be seen using the cancellation laws of retractions.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10681</anchor> <rss>erct-0027.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0027</addr>  <route>erct-0027.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">Contractible</link> types are closed under <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retracts</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0027.agda" type="external">erct-0027.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0025" title="Retract">retract</link> of <tex>A</tex> and <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>, then <tex>B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10682</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-0027</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>s \colon  B  \to  A</tex> be a section of <tex>r \colon  A \to  B</tex>; if <tex>a_0</tex> is the centre of contraction of <tex>A</tex>, then the centre of contraction of <tex>B</tex> is given by <tex>ra_0</tex>. For the rest, we use <ref addr="erct-0026" href="erct-0026.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>